                            <comment id="17298080" author="ifesdjeen" created="Tue, 9 Mar 2021 13:55:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the review. Committed to trunk with &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/6f13c864a02b32daa7696eca27431f5385a306df&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;6f13c864a02b32daa7696eca27431f5385a306df&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17298084" author="ifesdjeen" created="Tue, 9 Mar 2021 14:02:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the review! &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since bug is not present (i.e., there will be no assertion error) in 3.0 or 3.11 due to differences in code: empty bounds check was added in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14849&quot; title=&quot;some empty/invalid bounds aren&amp;#39;t caught by SelectStatement&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-14849&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-14849&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and 3.0 is even more different from 3.11, and won&apos;t fail even if assertion is added. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk with &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/9bc8d0b452aeb7aaa2005e710fc3de0998172738&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;9bc8d0b452aeb7aaa2005e710fc3de0998172738&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
